r:grantCategory>Research Grant</gtr:grantCategory><gtr:grantReference>ES/H000836/1</gtr:grantReference><gtr:abstractText>&lt;p>Obama?s 2008 presidential victory triggered a debate in Europe and the UK as to whether someone from an ethnic minority could achieve similar success in national politics.The 2010 General Election saw an increase in ethnic minority candidates and an almost double number of black and Asian MPs in the House of Commons.The series explored the prospects for ethnic minority representation in Britain and the barriers to achieving it at national and local levels. We found that although some progress has been made, factors at all levels of political system- from voters to party selectors- are hindering ethnic representation. &lt;br />&lt;br />&lt;/p>

